00:52:48,200 --> 00:52:51,682
is because too many people
have too much,

735
00:52:52,960 --> 00:52:55,930
and too many people have too little.

736
00:52:57,360 --> 00:53:00,011
So this is not over by any means.

737
00:53:00,440 --> 00:53:02,363
I agree with you.

738
00:53:04,400 --> 00:53:06,562
Hey! Hey, man!

739
00:53:06,920 --> 00:53:10,402
I am an American. I'm an American!

740
00:53:11,000 --> 00:53:12,968
You can't do this to me!

741
00:53:17,840 --> 00:53:19,046
Yes, General?

742
00:53:19,360 --> 00:53:21,567
Your associate seems to be missing.

743
00:53:22,640 --> 00:53:24,768
Well, if you find him,
have him give me a call.

744
00:53:25,280 --> 00:53:26,486
I will.

745
00:53:27,200 --> 00:53:29,806
We have located your Jack Begosian.

746
00:53:30,360 --> 00:53:34,160
There is $1 million for you
if you could dissuade

747
00:53:34,240 --> 00:53:38,643
Francisco Francis and Jack Begosian
from leaving Ecuador.

748
00:53:39,400 --> 00:53:42,927
Mr. Calder,
I believe they're worth a million each.

749
00:53:44,760 --> 00:53:46,364
I think you're right.

750
00:53:55,000 --> 00:53:57,571
<i>This is Jack Begosian, you're on the air.</i>

751
00:53:57,640 --> 00:53:59,722
<i>I was hoping
we could talk about eternity, Jack.</i>

752
00:54:00,520 --> 00:54:02,010
In what sense?

753
00:54:03,400 --> 00:54:05,243
<i>Do you think that
there's some aspect of ourselves</i>

754
00:54:05,320 --> 00:54:07,607
<i>that lives on, beyond this life?</i>

755
00:54:08,760 --> 00:54:12,207
<i>Yes, in the example we leave.</i>

756
00:54:13,920 --> 00:54:15,684
<i>What do you mean by that?</i>

757
00:54:16,920 --> 00:54:19,571
In the example you leave behind,
good or bad,

758
00:54:19,640 --> 00:54:21,529
that's what's remembered.

759
00:54:22,960 --> 00:54:25,645
<i>How do you want to be remembered, Jack?</i>

760
00:54:43,480 --> 00:54:47,371
<i>Well, I've done some things
that I'm not proud of.</i>

761
00:54:52,360 --> 00:54:54,442
<i>And will never be forgotten</i>

762
00:54:55,760 --> 00:54:57,762
<i>that are</i>

763
00:54:59,280 --> 00:55:01,442
impossible to forgive.

764
00:55:04,520 --> 00:55:08,366
<i>But I'm trying to do my best
to make amends and catch up</i>

765
00:55:11,720 --> 00:55:13,245
<i>and do my part.</i>

766
00:55:16,000 --> 00:55:17,809
<i>Thanks for the call.</i>

767
00:55:39,155 --> 00:55:40,680
You all right?

768
00:56:04,235 --> 00:56:05,316
Hold on.

769
00:56:10,275 --> 00:56:12,039
Put your gun down.

770
00:56:13,875 --> 00:56:15,036
Put your gun down!

771
00:56:23,955 --> 00:56:25,081
Hey!

772
00:57:09,435 --> 00:57:11,722
You'll get your money
by next Friday, Quako.

773
00:57:11,795 --> 00:57:14,560
I must tell you,
if this is forced to referendum,

774
00:57:14,635 --> 00:57:16,637
we cannot deliver on our agreement.

775
00:57:16,955 --> 00:57:20,323
<i>If this is not settled next Friday,
it may well go to referendum.</i>

776
00:57:20,395 --> 00:57:22,966
Rest assured, we'll be closed next week.

777
00:57:23,035 --> 00:57:24,878
<i>My associates and I
have always felt ClearBec</i>

778
00:57:24,955 --> 00:57:27,083
<i>was the most qualified company
with which to work.</i>

779
00:57:27,155 --> 00:57:28,236
Good.

780
00:57:28,355 --> 00:57:30,926
<i>But we've been hearing
some very unfavorable rumors</i>

781
00:57:30,995 --> 00:57:32,679
<i>regarding ClearBec in Ecuador.</i>

782
00:57:32,755 --> 00:57:33,881
It's nothing to worry about.

783
00:57:34,035 --> 00:57:37,596
<i>There are many companies
we can do this deal with, Bruce.</i>

784
00:57:37,755 --> 00:57:39,883
Rest assured we'll be closed.

785
00:57:39,955 --> 00:57:40,956
<i>Good.</i>

786
00:57:41,435 --> 00:57:43,642
We'll be awaiting your payment.

787
00:57:51,955 --> 00:57:55,084
<i>Roberto Shore de Canada.</i>
What is your real name?

788
00:57:58,755 --> 00:57:59,961
Jack.

789
00:58:02,155 --> 00:58:03,441
Jack Begosian.

790
00:58:04,195 --> 00:58:08,200
What brings you to these mountains,
Jack Begosian?

791
00:58:15,435 --> 00:58:18,245
I came looking for the survivors
of the attack at Tayca.

792
00:58:19,275 --> 00:58:21,403
Why? To what end?

793
00:58:22,835 --> 00:58:24,678
The people I work for,

794
00:58:25,715 --> 00:58:28,525
they want the world
to know the wrong that was done here,

795
00:58:29,155 --> 00:58:31,203
and the people who did it, charged.

796
00:58:31,275 --> 00:58:32,436
That's never gonna happen.

797
00:58:33,395 --> 00:58:36,638
ClearBec pays millions and millions
of dollars to the politicians here.

798
00:58:37,155 --> 00:58:38,236
They can be stopped.

799
00:58:38,715 --> 00:58:42,197
Okay. Well, I admire your spirit.

800
00:58:48,115 --> 00:58:49,241
Were you at Tayca?

801
00:58:49,675 --> 00:58:51,040
Yes, I was.

802
00:58:51,595 --> 00:58:52,835
There was a massacre there.

803
00:58:53,635 --> 00:58:55,046
I'm aware.

804
00:58:56,275 --> 00:58:58,164
What brought you there?

805
00:58:59,195 --> 00:59:00,685
My father lived in Tayca.

806
00:59:02,835 --> 00:59:04,837
We were visiting him when the typhus broke.

807
00:59:08,955 --> 00:59:13,404
I went to the offices of Inagua
to get some answers.

808
00:59:14,715 --> 00:59:16,080
I got none.

809
00:59:16,355 --> 00:59:19,165
So I broke in at night
and I got many answers.

810
00:59:24,555 --> 00:59:26,717
They say that I poisoned the water.

811
00:59:26,795 --> 00:59:29,002
They say that I attacked the army.

812
00:59:30,115 --> 00:59:31,480
Neither is true.

813
00:59:31,875 --> 00:59:33,206
It's a lie.

814
00:59:34,555 --> 00:59:35,841
I believe you.

815
00:59:41,315 --> 00:59:42,601
Let me help you, Francisco.

816
01:00:26,675 --> 01:00:28,040
Thank you.

817
01:00:34,035 --> 01:00:36,481
So, how do you know my name, Jack?

818
01:00:45,715 --> 01:00:49,162
You were the founder and leader
of La Vida Campesina.

819
01:00:53,635 --> 01:00:55,524
I didn't lead them well.

820
01:00:58,075 --> 01:01:00,442
The movement almost died underneath me.

821
01:01:00,875 --> 01:01:05,517
I learned that nothing grows
out of the barrel of a gun

822
01:01:06,835 --> 01:01:08,280
but violence.

823
01:01:09,155 --> 01:01:12,602
And that Mao was wrong and Gandhi is right.

824
01:01:14,475 --> 01:01:17,718
You said you found answers
when you broke into the offices of Inagua.

825
01:01:20,235 --> 01:01:22,636
ClearBec's filtration system
is what caused the typhus.

826
01:01:23,995 --> 01:01:25,520
You have proof?

827
01:01:25,675 --> 01:01:28,406
I have their records. I downloaded them.
I have them over here.

828
01:01:28,795 --> 01:01:30,399
Then come with me.

829
01:01:30,475 --> 01:01:33,160
Be a witness against ClearBec.
Tell your story.

830
01:01:33,275 --> 01:01:34,686
Francisco...

831
01:01:35,515 --> 01:01:36,960
Come with me.

832
01:01:37,035 --> 01:01:38,480
Francisco...

833
01:01:40,475 --> 01:01:41,761
I don't trust him.

834
01:01:41,835 --> 01:01:42,882
We don't know him.

835
01:01:42,955 --> 01:01:45,845
It's fine.
I'll tell him.

836
01:01:50,155 --> 01:01:52,601
My wife, she doesn't trust you.

837
01:01:53,795 --> 01:01:54,796
I know.

838
01:01:55,195 --> 01:01:56,835
She thinks that our family won't be safe.

839
01:01:58,315 --> 01:01:59,805
Is your family safe here?

840
01:02:01,235 --> 01:02:03,158
How long can they live like this?

841
01:02:03,235 --> 01:02:05,203
How long can anyone live?

842
01:02:06,235 --> 01:02:08,158
The answer's always the same, until we die.

843
01:02:09,835 --> 01:02:10,961
Come with me.

844
01:02:12,675 --> 01:02:15,838
We will stop ClearBec from doing what
they did here in other countries.

845
01:02:16,435 --> 01:02:18,756
How do you know they'll listen to us?

846
01:02:19,795 --> 01:02:21,320
You have to trust me.

847
01:02:22,635 --> 01:02:24,080
Francisco...

848
01:02:25,435 --> 01:02:26,925
You must trust me.

849
01:02:27,155 --> 01:02:28,805
You must trust me!

850
01:02:45,755 --> 01:02:48,520
Forgive me.
I lost control.

851
01:02:50,355 --> 01:02:52,926
I had to do it.
I lost my family.

852
01:02:56,115 --> 01:02:58,925
I share your pain.

853
01:02:59,875 --> 01:03:02,003
I understand your pain.

854
01:03:42,635 --> 01:03:44,524
I put my trust in you.

855
01:03:52,995 --> 01:03:54,326
Thank you.

856
01:03:57,555 --> 01:03:58,761
We need to move now.

857
01:04:32,715 --> 01:04:34,638
Get your family out!

858
01:04:35,155 --> 01:04:36,725
- Mama!
- Mia! Mia!

859
01:04:42,035 --> 01:04:43,924
Go, go, go!

860
01:04:56,235 --> 01:04:58,636
Come on, come on.
Come on, come on.

861
01:05:32,635 --> 01:05:33,716
Mama!

862
01:06:26,795 --> 01:06:28,240
Jesus, are you all right?

863
01:06:29,435 --> 01:06:31,164
Are you both all right?

864
01:06:31,235 --> 01:06:32,202
Listen to your mother.

865
01:06:35,915 --> 01:06:37,405
I have to go back.

866
01:06:39,875 --> 01:06:42,640
Yes. Go.

867
01:06:45,035 --> 01:06:46,275
Come on, let's go! Let's move! Move...

868
01:06:46,355 --> 01:06:48,483
- I can't. I gotta go back!
- What?

869
01:06:48,915 --> 01:06:49,882
He has to go back.

870
01:06:49,955 --> 01:06:51,605
He has to help
them or else they'll die.

871
01:06:51,675 --> 01:06:52,835
He must not go back up there.

872
01:06:52,955 --> 01:06:54,719
Please, please, take care of my family.

873
01:06:55,035 --> 01:06:57,236
If something happens to you,
the truth will not get out.

874
01:06:58,395 --> 01:06:59,920
She has truth.

875
01:07:02,795 --> 01:07:04,718
Keep moving downhill.

876
01:07:05,595 --> 01:07:07,757
- Jesus!
- Mama!

877
01:07:33,875 --> 01:07:35,286
It's okay, it's okay.

878
01:07:44,995 --> 01:07:46,360
Here you go. You ready?

879
01:07:46,435 --> 01:07:47,402
Yes.

880
01:07:58,155 --> 01:08:00,237
- Shoot to kill. Got it?
- Yes.

881
01:08:00,315 --> 01:08:02,124
Wait for my first shot.

882
01:08:56,355 --> 01:08:58,596
Okay, get them out of here!
Get them out of here!

883
01:09:07,795 --> 01:09:10,082
Francisco! Your family, let's go!

884
01:09:10,675 --> 01:09:11,961
Let's move!

885
01:09:12,795 --> 01:09:15,366
Francisco, we gotta move!

886
01:10:04,235 --> 01:10:06,203
It's all clear up there.

887
01:10:06,355 --> 01:10:09,086
Okay? Rest up a little, lie down.

888
01:10:17,195 --> 01:10:18,720
Francisco.

889
01:10:19,115 --> 01:10:21,004
May I sit for a moment?

890
01:10:21,515 --> 01:10:22,721
Of course.

891
01:10:39,795 --> 01:10:41,843
There's something you need to know.

892
01:10:44,795 --> 01:10:45,876
What?

893
01:10:50,315 --> 01:10:52,283
I worked for the CIA in South America.

894
01:10:55,675 --> 01:10:56,836
I see.

895
01:10:57,755 --> 01:11:00,998
I'm the man responsible
for sending you to prison.

896
01:11:09,275 --> 01:11:10,686
Well, then...

897
01:11:12,715 --> 01:11:14,126
I'm indebted to you.

898
01:11:16,915 --> 01:11:18,485
I don't understand.

899
01:11:20,675 --> 01:11:25,602
When I went to prison,
it changed the way I thought.

900
01:11:27,435 --> 01:11:29,403
I wrote this book, <i>Presence is Born.</i>

901
01:11:30,635 --> 01:11:33,002
I published it under a pseudonym.

902
01:11:35,755 --> 01:11:37,837
You wrote Presence is Born?

903
01:11:38,475 --> 01:11:39,522
Yes.

904
01:11:42,355 --> 01:11:45,996
That book was very successful.
It was a best-seller.

905
01:11:47,155 --> 01:11:52,082
Yes, I gave all the rights to that
book to la Vida Campesina.

906
01:11:54,435 --> 01:11:55,766
You regret that?

907
01:11:56,555 --> 01:11:57,636
No.

908
01:11:59,035 --> 01:12:02,801
La Vida Campesina
is 150 million people strong.

909
01:12:04,035 --> 01:12:10,077
It's a movement of peasants and farmers
who are fighting,

910
01:12:10,755 --> 01:12:13,361
unlike me, peacefully,

911
01:12:14,275 --> 01:12:16,155
for the integrity
of their land and their water,

912
01:12:17,195 --> 01:12:21,484
and for the needs of all their children,
and the children to come.

913
01:12:29,995 --> 01:12:31,360
Do you have children?

914
01:12:32,435 --> 01:12:35,439
I have a boy. His name is Jason.

915
01:12:43,715 --> 01:12:45,638
"You will be my son forever and ever."

916
01:12:47,275 --> 01:12:48,800
I wrote that when my son was born.

917
01:13:02,675 --> 01:13:04,598
Nothing will ever change that.

918
01:13:07,595 --> 01:13:08,756
Nothing.

919
01:13:09,755 --> 01:13:11,200
I'm sorry, my friend.

920
01:13:13,875 --> 01:13:15,115
It was a gift.

921
01:13:18,275 --> 01:13:20,039
It was a gift to me.

922
01:13:24,995 --> 01:13:26,201
We need to move on.

923
01:14:02,635 --> 01:14:04,239
I have a vehicle waiting for us up here.

924
01:14:12,315 --> 01:14:14,363
Give me your hand. Come on.

925
01:14:45,315 --> 01:14:47,397
Francisco, let's go!
We have to get out of here!

926
01:14:47,475 --> 01:14:49,239
Francisco! Francisco!

927
01:15:43,955 --> 01:15:46,322
<i>The people down here regard you a hero.</i>

928
01:15:46,395 --> 01:15:48,762
<i>They call you Francisco Francis.</i>

929
01:15:49,115 --> 01:15:50,560
<i>I was born in San Francisco.</i>

930
01:15:51,715 --> 01:15:54,798
<i>You received your Ph.D.
in Environmental Studies.</i>

931
01:15:54,875 --> 01:15:57,355
<i>You came down here
with Greenpeace to South America,</i>

932
01:15:57,435 --> 01:16:01,281
<i>and now you're serving
11 years in a very tough prison.</i>

933
01:16:01,955 --> 01:16:03,036
<i>Yes.</i>

934
01:16:03,515 --> 01:16:05,961
<i>How did you become involved
in the South American water wars</i>

935
01:16:06,035 --> 01:16:07,844
<i>that resulted in you becoming incarcerated?</i>

936
01:16:08,515 --> 01:16:10,165
How could I not get involved?

937
01:16:10,235 --> 01:16:13,637
It became illegal for farmers
to collect rain water

938
01:16:13,715 --> 01:16:17,561
because ClearBec owned
all the water rights in the whole country.

939
01:16:17,635 --> 01:16:20,002
That's like saying, "I own God."

940
01:16:21,075 --> 01:16:25,763
<i>Do you have any regrets
about what you did, and being here today?</i>

941
01:16:27,555 --> 01:16:29,398
I regret the violence.

942
01:16:30,075 --> 01:16:31,486
I regret

943
01:16:34,275 --> 01:16:38,280
not having enough knowledge

944
01:16:42,275 --> 01:16:46,644
to make the proper choices

945
01:16:47,275 --> 01:16:50,836
<i>that would have helped the people.</i>

946
01:16:51,835 --> 01:16:53,360
<i>I regret that.</i>

947
01:16:56,795 --> 01:16:57,796
Hello?

948
01:16:59,475 --> 01:17:01,637
Hello, can you hear me? Hello!

949
01:17:02,035 --> 01:17:04,003
Mom, it's for you.

950
01:17:06,155 --> 01:17:09,045
<i>Thank you, sweetie. Thank you.</i>

951
01:17:09,915 --> 01:17:11,076
<i>Hello?</i>

952
01:17:11,435 --> 01:17:14,245
Yes, this is Jack.
I've found Francisco Francis.

953
01:17:17,875 --> 01:17:20,719
Yes. Is... Is he...

954
01:17:20,755 --> 01:17:23,884
He's alive. Listen very carefully.

955
01:17:23,915 --> 01:17:25,917
I need you to call the number I gave you.

956
01:17:26,475 --> 01:17:28,477
<i>Tell them there are four people coming in.</i>

957
01:17:29,035 --> 01:17:31,925
I'm gonna text you the names,
confirm you receive them,

958
01:17:31,995 --> 01:17:34,362
<i>forward and delete. You got that?</i>

959
01:17:34,835 --> 01:17:35,996
And... And...

960
01:17:37,555 --> 01:17:38,556
Hello?

961
01:17:40,155 --> 01:17:40,655
<i>Jack?</i>

962
01:17:47,275 --> 01:17:48,436
<i>Yes?</i>

963
01:17:48,595 --> 01:17:51,883
Well, looks like
you're gonna get your money's worth.

964
01:17:56,915 --> 01:18:01,443
When that plane lands,
we've got to prevent Begosian

965
01:18:01,515 --> 01:18:05,440
from bringing Francis anywhere where he
could cause any more damage,

966
01:18:05,555 --> 01:18:09,196
because, Bruce, if we
don't, we are finished.

967
01:18:11,155 --> 01:18:13,920
We've gone too far, Doug, too far.

968
01:18:14,795 --> 01:18:16,638
Bruce, listen to me.

969
01:18:17,475 --> 01:18:20,206
Francisco Francis has many enemies.

970
01:18:20,755 --> 01:18:24,362
Violent people
who will stop at nothing to eliminate him.

971
01:18:24,915 --> 01:18:27,077
They hired an assassin, Tor.

972
01:18:27,795 --> 01:18:32,676
The assassin will kill Jack Begosian
and Francisco Francis.

973
01:18:33,075 --> 01:18:36,522
Our security will kill the assassin

974
01:18:37,155 --> 01:18:39,965
because they're there protecting Morgan.

975
01:18:41,155 --> 01:18:43,806
And Morgan will still be a liability.

976
01:18:56,035 --> 01:18:57,958
Am I your enemy now, Bruce?

977
01:18:58,795 --> 01:19:00,923
No, but...

978
01:19:01,915 --> 01:19:04,156
What you're doing will
bring down ClearBec, Morgan.

979
01:19:05,075 --> 01:19:07,316
Maybe ClearBec deserves
to be brought down.

980
01:19:08,155 --> 01:19:11,238
You're forgetting
all the good that we have done.

981
01:19:11,795 --> 01:19:15,845
You're forgetting those
thousands of towns and villages

982
01:19:15,915 --> 01:19:18,964
that we provided water
for that otherwise wouldn't have had it.

983
01:19:19,035 --> 01:19:21,561
You're forgetting about all the lives
of the children that we saved.

984
01:19:21,635 --> 01:19:23,046
No, I'm not.

985
01:19:23,475 --> 01:19:25,762
But I'm not forgetting
about Ecuador either.

986
01:19:27,555 --> 01:19:29,125
I'm sorry that that happened, I am.

987
01:19:30,835 --> 01:19:32,755
<i>But you're forgetting
to look at the big picture.</i>

988
01:19:33,555 --> 01:19:35,683
We have to move on,
we have to move forward.

989
01:19:35,755 --> 01:19:36,881
